I met this guy in the small lanes in Lucknow’s Old City. His family used to make these pure silver jootis aka Nagras for the Nawabs but now he’s makes them for brides. The cost of making is high, demand is low. Also he’s the last person in his family making this so this art will die with him unless someone learns it from him. - +91 88405 51025 -this is his son’s number if you need to make an order, they can ship it anywhere. 

I would say this is a better investment than some designer brand shoe 👟 what do you think??? 

This man is the Indian Jimmy Choooo? ;) or better!!!! #silverjootis #nakashiart #silvernagras thanks @taha_ahmadlucknow for helping me shoot!

What is the one place you go to and feel a lot of positive energy???

They say Kasar Devi Temple sits on a magnetic field as powerful as Machu Picchu and Stonehenge.
But for me, it wasn’t about energy fields or science.
It was about what I felt.

📍Kasar Devi Temple, Almora – one of the most peaceful and powerful places. If you’re searching for clarity, healing, or just some quiet… this is your sign to go.

#KasarDevi #UttarakhandTravel

What’s one thing in your home you know could be more eco-friendly… but you haven’t changed yet? How will you change it? 👀 and what product from this reel would you use? 

For me, 
AC, Detergent bottles, wasted water, toxic batteries… felt like hell! 
Especially after visiting a couple who live with no electricity, no fridge, no flush—
I couldn’t unsee it.

So I made 3 small swaps from Amazon:
🧼 Biodegradable cleaning pills
🔋 Aloe vera batteries
🌿 Khus curtains (the best natural AC!)

No big renovations. Just thoughtful choices.
Now my home feels lighter, calmer, cleaner—and so does my conscience.

What would your first swap be?
Drop it in the comments 💚👇

#HarDinBehtar #GlimmerOfTheDay #gotd

Yesterday’s Air India plane crash broke my heart.
I’ve been on hundreds of flights. It could’ve been any of us.
Just a reminder of how fragile life really is.
Of how little control we truly have.
Of how much we take for granted.

And then… I remembered this moment.
At the Golu Devta Temple in Uttarakhand—where people write letters to God.
Not just prayers, but actual letters. About love. Injustice. Loss. Hopes.
Even court cases and wedding invites.

And when a wish comes true, they come back and tie a bell.
I didn’t tie mine. Not yet.
But I hope I get to.
Because life is unpredictable—and this temple reminded me that sometimes, all we can do is… surrender.

So if you’re feeling heavy, grieving, or just holding your breath after the news…
Come here.
Write.
Manifest.
Pray.

BUT DO NOT TURN THIS INTO A TOURISM DESTINATION OR THE CHARM OF THIS PLACE and maybe even the power will fade. 

If your Therapist says write a diary or manifest - tell them - 
Uttrakhand has been manifesting for centuries! 

#Manifestation #HealingPlaces #LetterToGod
